				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$0^\circ$$\end{document}. Then the bottom TiN NRA was deposited at a deposition angle of 84Â°. In order to control the sputtering flux rate, a stainless steel plate was placed parallel to the substrate at a distance 10Â mm from it. After the deposition of bottom layer, the substrate was rotated by 90Â° to deposit the upper layer. The upper TiN NRA was grown at a deposition angle of 88Â° and the distance between the substrate and the stainless steel plate was 8Â mm.
